parameters: Little girl Relm: 'Daddy, are you working again today...?'

Relm's father: I have to work today, tomorrow, and the day
after tomorrow to earn money for our living expenses.

Relm's father: Hmph, if only you were a boy, I could have
put you to work.

Relm was born as the youngest of six siblings. All of her
siblings, except for Relm, were older by several years.

Relm's father was a road repair worker who was assigned to
repair roads throughout the empire. He treated his siblings
as apprentices, successors, and labor force. Therefore, he
had a cold attitude towards Relm, who was deemed useless.

The death of his beloved wife during Relm's birth was the
cause of a situation that was close to neglecting Relm's
upbringing. While the fathers were at work, Relm spent her
time reading books given to her by her older brothers.

The origin of Relm's obsession with books later on is
influenced by her childhood experiences. For Relm, books
were not only something to read, but also her only friends.
